      "id": "397c766306e77f24e4a128894785a58ad605c40a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2014-12-29 18:31:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI would prefer that we not kill obd_valid since this gives a hint about which flags are to be used in a variable names \"flags\". Also I think that instead of just doing s/obd_off/u64/ we should see which of these values should be of type loff_t and which should really be u64.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "23ea3dba2136bd01355556510e1a1eb287cc8ffc",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2015-01-05 22:15:06.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nHow a enum for obd_vaild? I have a feeling a lot of places in the code use u64/u32 instead of loff_t. Should open a separate ticket for that. I feel that should be handled with a different patch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "799baa39c1260388ad0392f29a0a0865f023221e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2015-01-05 22:22:55.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> How a enum for obd_vaild? I have a feeling a lot of places in the code use u64/u32 instead of loff_t. Should open a separate ticket for that. I feel that should be handled with a different patch.\n\nYes but obd_size -> loff_t should happen before obd_size -> u64.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "7ef1208eb830c1b553afe3a9789d7952c48ec525",
      "author": {
